column153: Positive identification is impossible from the photo since it was taken on a white wall at night, when all of the Hemidactylus turn their lightest color and are nearly translucent. However, knowing that both H. garnotii and H. turcicus have disappeared in Miami over the last 20 years, possibly because of the more recent introduction of H. mabouia, it is likely this species. You would need to secure a voucher specimen to know for sure (Dr. Kenney Krysko, University of Florida, personal communication).
